cmCourseInfo.description: The representation of the classical world and historical events in film. How the Greek and Roman world is reconstructed by filmmakers, their use of spectacle, costume and furnishings, and the influence of archaeology on their portrayals. Films will be studied critically for historical accuracy and faithfulness to classical sources. Same as HISB12H3
cmCourseInfo.title: The Ancient World in Film
